 Existing Lucene core tests already require JVM module opens for reflective/internal JDK access used by RamUsageEstimator and MMapDirectory.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Keep or add JVM test arguments when exercising Lucene internals that inspect object layout or unmap mmap buffers: --add-opens=java.base/java.nio=ALL-UNNAMED and --add-opens=java.base/jdk.internal.ref=ALL-UNNAMED. The 6.0.0 compile failure is an API change: custom AttributeImpl subclasses must implement reflectWith(AttributeReflector). Do not add lucene-analyzers-common just to use StandardAnalyzer; core coverage can use a small custom Analyzer/TokenStream instead.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Many Lucene examples use StandardAnalyzer from lucene-analyzers-common, but adding that dependency would broaden the target beyond lucene-core and is not required for meaningful core coverage.\",\n    \"The reported javac failure is caused by Lucene 6's AttributeImpl API change, so setup alone will not fix compilation.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04ae888ec86c818d016a3fae4583d48196b1ffda4b6d20c994\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1394, "output": 1467, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29485, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782558255549, "responseId": "resp_04ae888ec86c818d016a3fae3035d08196bf056e7fa02ec449"}, "toolResults": []}
